cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image restoration using deep CNNs and proposes a spatial attention mechanism based on the dependency of human contrast sensitivity on spatial frequency. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of pre-trained CNNs and optimization techniques, which are common in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed technique using subjective human assessment, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new loss function, which can be considered as a neural network architecture design, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
